  <description type="morphology">Stems erect or spreading, rarely decumbent; herbage glabrous, eglandular. Leaf blades narrowly oblanceolate, 15–30(–40) × 3–8 mm, not thick-fleshy, margins entire or with 1–2 pairs of teeth or shallow lobes distally. Heads in corymbiform arrays. Corollas 5.5–6.5. Cypselae 2.5–3.5 mm. 2n = 24.</description>
